# Architecture & Folder Structure

- **App boundaries**
  - `src/app/` — routes/pages (Next.js)
  - `src/components/` — reusable UI components
  - `src/features/<feature>/` — feature modules (invoice, clients, settings)
  - `src/server/` — server actions, API handlers, DB access
  - `src/lib/` — shared utilities (pure, no framework coupling)
  - `src/config/` — limits, tier rules, environment parsing
  - `src/types/` — shared TS types
- **Feature module convention**
  - `model.ts` (types + domain logic)
  - `service.ts` (orchestration; calls DB/external)
  - `ui/` (feature UI components)
  - `__tests__/` (unit tests close to feature)
- **Data access**
  - No raw DB calls from UI components; go through `src/server/*`.
- **Environment**
  - Centralize env parsing in one place; no `process.env.X` scattered.

